<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued January 01 at 10:45AM MST until January 02 at 6:00AM MST by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM MST SUNDAY...
...WIND CHILL ADVISORY WILL EXPIRE AT 11 AM MST THIS MORNING...
* WHAT...Blowing snow developing. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph,
with gusts in excess of 60 mph possible along the Rocky Mountain
Front.
* WHERE...Lewis and Clark County and the Rocky Mountain Front,
Cascade, and Judith Basin.
* WHEN...Until 6 AM MST Sunday.
* IMPACTS...Widespread blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility at times.</description>
<instruction>Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas. The latest
road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1 or visiting the MDT
Road Report website.</instruction>
